      The tax angle
   =20
 =20
Elsewhere in privateering, here=E2=80=99s an apparently real notice from In=
terfax-Ukraine:No need to declare captured Russian tanks, other equipment o=
f invaders as income =E2=80=93 NAPCUkraine's National Agency for the Protec=
tion against Corruption (NAPC) has declared that captured Russian tanks and=
 other equipment are not subject to declaration."Have you captured a Russia=
n tank or armored personnel carrier and are worried about how to declare it=
? Keep calm and continue to defend the Motherland! There is no need to decl=
are the captured Russian tanks and other equipment, because the cost of thi=
s ... does not exceed 100 living wages (UAH 248,100)," NAPC's press service=
 said. =E2=80=A6"Speaking by the letter of the law, combat trophies are not=
 subject to reflection in the declaration for the following reasons: they w=
ere acquired not as a result of the conclusion of any type of transaction, =
but in connection with the full-scale aggression of the Russian Federation =
on February 24, 2022 against the independent and sovereign Ukrainian state =
as a continuation the insidious attack of the Russian Federation on Ukraine=
 launched in 2014. Thanks to the courage and victory of the defenders of th=
e Ukrainian state, enemy military equipment usually comes to you already de=
stroyed and disabled, which makes it impossible to evaluate it in accordanc=
e with the law On the valuation of property, property rights and profession=
al valuation activities in Ukraine. Therefore, it is also impossible to fin=
d out how much such property costs,=E2=80=9D the NACP said.This strikes me =
as sensible tax policy. For one thing, taxing anything tends to discourage =
that thing, and clearly the Ukrainian government wants to encourage its cit=
izens to capture Russian tanks. For another thing, surely the stated reason=
ing is correct and it is hard to get a market value for a disabled Russian =
tank; if you can=E2=80=99t sell it in a ready market it is a bit harsh to h=
ave to pay taxes on it. Presumably the main motive for this press release i=
s not so much to get the tax policy right but rather to demonstrate some in=
credible wartime sangfroid, but the tax policy also seems right.
